text: Authentic thai food served with Thai hospitality. Freshly prepared, with generous serving sizes, and super delicious (aroi maak!). Will visit again soon.

This dried curry chicken rice is a must to eat. Surprisingly good and strong taste yet not spicy. The Tom yum soup is good and creamy too. I ever tried their mango rice too. Sweet cold mango with warm rice and coconut milk top on it. Too bad. Today never order. ðŸ¤£ðŸ¤£ scary heaty.

The spoon they gave for grab food is broken.
I got $4 green milk tea and $7.90 chicken basil rice. Food taste average. Drink got alot.

Fair priced and good portion. Prawn Tom Yam with rice $6.50 - Came 4 large prawnss! Chicken Basil with wgg $6.50 n Thai Fish Cake $4.50..  Total $17.50 for 2 paxs. They have Thai Milk Tea too. We had the ice lemon tea from drinks stall $1.70 for big mug! Only setback was - No beer at drinks stall

Food was nice . I only order kra pow as this is the usual food I like and can see the skill of the chef. Most basic thai food .  This place no pork so they use chicken .
